<div class=3D"mktoText" id=3D"free_text249349de-acde-4ce2-9186-b79cb33c8d97=
">
 The latest release introduces new ways to manage app state and user intera=
ction. Here are some highlights:=20
<br />=20
<ul>=20
<li>&#127871; Introducing dynamic containers: <span style=3D"font-family: '=
Courier New';">st.tabs, st.popover</span>, and <span style=3D"font-family: =
'Courier New';">st.expander</span> can rerun the app when they are opened o=
r closed by setting the <span style=3D"font-family: 'Courier New';">on_chan=
ge</span> parameter. If a key is also provided, you can programmatically op=
en and close them, too</li>=20
<li>&#128391; Announcing widget binding! Most non-trigger widgets have a <s=
pan style=3D"font-family: 'Courier New';">bind</span> parameter to simplify=
 syncing widget state with query parameters</li>=20
<li><span style=3D"font-family: 'Courier New';">=09 &#128279; st.image</spa=
n> has a <span style=3D"font-family: 'Courier New';">link</span> parameter =
to make images clickable with HTTP/HTTPS URLs</li>=20
<li><span style=3D"font-family: 'Courier New';">&#129399; st.Page</span> ha=
s a <span style=3D"font-family: 'Courier New';">visibility</span> parameter=
 that lets you hide pages in the navigation menu while keeping them routabl=
e</li>=20
</ul>=20
